@node not04 "ALIVE MEDIASOFT - RELEASE ANNOUNCEMENT 23RD MARCH 2000"
             ALIVE MEDIASOFT - RELEASE ANNOUNCEMENT 23RD MARCH 2000
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

   - TITLE: Super Taekwondo Master
   - PRICE: £14.99
   - RELEASE DATE: April 2000
   - BRIEF DESCRIPTION: 2D Beat 'em up
   - REQUIRES: AGA CDrom

Super Taekwondo Master is a 2d action simulator for 1 or 2 players. Fully
digitised characters, superimposed into a computer generated world in spendid
graphical glory. The look is similar to that of Mortal Kombat, but the gameplay
is more realistic. There's no hurling fireballs at your enemy here, you must be
a competant fighter to take on these guys. Strategy and skill are utmost
importance in Taekwondo Master.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

   - TITLE: Cedric and the Search for the Magic Sceptre
   - PRICE: £14.99
   - RELEASE DATE: Out Now
   - BRIEF DESCRIPTION: Jump and Run Adventure
   - REQUIRES: AGA CDrom

Accompany Cedric on his dangerous way through 11 giant levels searching for the
lost sceptre. Explore islands, search through cities, survive the sudden
winters, cross huge lava lakes, fight against the mighty bosses and seek out
justice.

You play the title role of our hero Cedric who is a poor apprentice blacksmith
working for The King. You are madly in love with the kings daughter - as she is
with you - but her father will not permit her marriage to a peasant boy. Then
the day comes where you are given the opportunity to gain credability with your
would-be father in law and rescue his magic sceptre which has been stolen by his
arch enemy Edi W Le Mac. So, you start you quest stranded in the woods after
being robbed of all your possesions. You begin your journey across the lands
looking for the magic sceptre, fighting bad guys bare handed.

As you can see from the screenshots, this is played on platforms similar to
Shadow of the Beast or Lion Heart. However, the action forms only part of the
game as the rest is played in a traditional point-and-click stlye like Monkey
Island, whereby you can hold objects you find in an inventory to be used later
on in your quest. You can look at items, talk to characters, give, drop, take,
use etc. All the usual point and click features incorporated into an exciting
non-stop action game. You play using a joypad (Cedric is also CD32 pad
compatible), and there's no set route so you're open to explore each level at
your leisure.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

