23 March 2000 - The Latest News

I regretfully announce that Payback has been delayed again - it will now not be
available until late May at the earliest. This is partly due to continued delays
getting hold of a graphics card and partly due to the sheer size and complexity
of the levels. Despite this, a lot of new features have been added this month:

   - Hidden mission have been added. I don't want to give too much away, but I'm
     sure you'll enjoy discovering them!
   - Lots of new graphics for the levels have been drawn.
   - The scripting language has been expanded to include lots of new 'triggers',
     which will allow more varied missions.
   - A lot more of the city has been designed.
   - New 'secret' vehicles have been added.
   - Lots of bugs have been fixed.
   - The collision detection system has been made a lot more reliable.
   - Textures are now compressed so that they use half the memory they used to.
   - An options screen has been added.
   - More sound effects have been added. For example, you can now hear bullets
     ricocheting off the walls, or crashing noises as you plough into a tree.
     The sound of your footsteps changes as you walk over different surfaces.

Well, that's it for this time - look forward to seeing you next update!

James Daniels
Apex Designs

