Hello and welcome to the 20th issue of AmiChannel News.

I know that this issue is a little bit late, but only a little little bit, eh!
The reason for this tiny delay has been the Amiga2k show held in San Louis on
April 1-2. I was expecting reports from the show and confirmations of the things
which came from there, but Amiga Inc is lacking of professionalism.

As probably you know by now, "Fool's Day" is a day devoted to say false things.
Taking into account that the news we hear from the very beginning came from only
one source, you can imagine that everybody thought that they could be false. And
no move in the Amiga website. Not even a proper press release. This is not the
prfessionalism you can expect from a today serious company.

But apart from that, there are a lot of news, all of them you can read in this
issue. The development box has been unveiled, although it is not ready for
release. As expected, the devbox is just a PC with AMD K6-2 500 Mhz, 64 Mb RAM
and GeForce 256. Not a problem for me. The Eleate OS will run hosted on a Red
Hat Linux system. As we are speaking of the devbox it is not a bad thing. The
problem is that the user system to be released who knows when wil run hosted on
a Linux system.

I'm sorry to say that this could be the end of the Amiga as an independent
system. Amiga will lost its identity. Instead of "trying to change the world",
Amiga Inc "embrace Linux" for its success. So, we are in the same position in
Collas times, but this time it has not been promised a hardware box. And we have
lost one year.

